author: @gwanghyeongim768
text: For those who want to run script in sublime text on Mac, install one package and you're good to go. To do that follow these: 1. Open Command Palette(In Menu > Tools > Command Palette or simply type shift command p) 2. Type install package and choose 'Package Control: Install Package' 3. Type 'SublimeREPL' and install it by hitting it 4. Open Build(Menu > Tools > Build or type comma b). You just ran your code in sublime text.
